OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHeat wave in India leaves  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fmillions struggling to cope
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, India's weather department has issued a
OL,6, severe heatwave warning as temperatures
OL,7, soar, throwing millions of lives and   
OL,8, livelihoods out of gear.               
OL,10,F"Temperatures are rising rapidly in the
OL,11,Fcountry, and rising much earlier than  
OL,12,Fusual," Prime Minister Narendra Modi   
OL,13,Ftold state chief ministers on          
OL,14,FWednesday.                             
OL,16,FThe India Meteorological Department    
OL,17,F(IMD) has forecast a gradual rise in   
OL,18,Fmaximum temperatures by 2-4C over most 
OL,19,Fparts of north-western and central     
OL,20,FIndia this week, with "no large change 
OL,21,Fthereafter".                           
